{"id": 4190, "title": "Ticket #4190: Our file transfer plugins should support output URLs", "description": "<blockquote>\nJobs can specify supply a URL for output files. Our curl plugin should support that usage, at least for the file type.\n\n<p>The plugin can check which argument looks like a URL and do an input or output transfer as appropriate.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2014-Apr-11 16:45:26 by zmiller:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE REVIEW</strong>:  Overall looks fine.  Currently HTCondor assumes two slashes are part of the URL, so you could add that to the \"file:\" test.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body><blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"../files/821/plugin.patch\">plugin.patch</a>\n2485 bytes added by jfrey on 2014-Feb-03 22:39:59 UTC.\n<br/>\nPatch to support output URLs in the curl plugin.<br/>\n</li></ul>\n</blockquote></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Apr-18 16:48</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/bdf306f72714022b93f77d47d53415dbb88d8a3e\">[39993]</a></span>: minor spelling change for 8.1.6 version history item <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4190\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4190'); return false;\" title=\"Our file transfer plugins should support output URLs\">#4190</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Apr-14 16:27</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/e3914636d5ecc497ff54c6ad173